title: For Sale:  R.S.Braverman "Stinger" Pen Gun *Rare* 22lr
postcontent: This is a rare R.S.Braverman "Stinger" Pen Gun in 22lr. It's a single shot pen gun, approved by the ATF as a pistol, because it cannot be fired unless opened into an L shape. After opening, the pistol is cocked and a small trigger folds out and it's ready to fire. There is a safety in the form of a rotating collar in the middle of the body. All stainless steel construction, with a nickel plated barrel, and very high quality made completely in the U.S.A. These were made for approximately ten years, ending in 2004 when the company shut down, so they only go up in value every year. This one is in perfect shape, only minor handling marks, with original box, and even the original cardboard sleeve w/matching serial number!

title: For Sale:  WTS: Rare Finn P-27 M91 Mosin Nagant
postcontent:
Hi everyone! I'm selling a rare P-series Finnish Mosin. This is an older CAI import. The history behind these rifles were either captured or bought from the Russians and other Eastern European countries in the early 1920s. The bores on these were considered worn out and a sleeve was placed in the barrel. While the barrels were manufactured on those dates, they were known to be placed on rifles until supply was exhausted during WWII and the Continuation War.

This was an early attempt to rework these rifles before they began to manufacture new barrels. Known variants are the P-26, P-27, and P-28 with a production of approx. 10,000 rifles. These rifles are known to be as accurate as their descendants and great rugged rifles. Range test tended to prove it!

Condition is fair with light to  moderate pitting on the receiver. Bore appears to be frosted but with good lands/grooves. The receiver dates to 1919, so possibly a purchased rifle in the '20s or captured in the Winter War/Continuation War. Stock is a one piece. Unfortunately the stock was stripped of it's finish but the cartouches were untouched. Shot 1-2 inch groups at 100 yards (offhand). Please email or give me a call at REDACTED for any further questions! Lev

Pictures to be added!

title: For Sale:  Molot VEPR Pioneer 223/5.56 AK VEPR-801
postcontent: Built on the same standard as the RPK style machine guns, Vepr Pioneer is 50% more reinforced than a standard, stamped AK rifle. Each rifle has been manufactured using state of the art technology, effectively creating a heavy duty piece that will last through not just a lifetime but for many generations to come. The RPK-style barrels are hammer forged and chrome lined using techniques that make them four to five times stronger than a standard AK or RPK barrel.Vepr Pioneer in.223 Rem caliber boasts a front sight / gas block combination and a single piece of walnut as the furniture. The buttstock is built in the “Monte-Carlo” style. The tip of the RPK style barrel is vented to create functionality as if there was a muzzle break attached. A unique feature of this firearm is the removable trigger housing. Also, there is no scope rail attached to the side of the receiver. Instead, there is a rail system built into the receiver directly, just above the fire control group and below the top cover. A scope mount (not included) can be attached to this rail system.Each rifle comes with high quality, beautifully crafted walnut furniture as well as a rear sight with adjustable windage. They are shipped with one 10-round magazine, a cleaning rod, and a cleaning kit.
